# Design foundations — Storybook catalogs

When adding design tokens or icons, update the matching Storybook catalog in the same change.

## Colors → `tokens.stories.tsx`

When adding or renaming a color token (e.g. in `globals.css` `@theme` or `:root` CSS variables), add a swatch to the `Colors` story in `src/components/foundations/tokens.stories.tsx`.

```tsx
// ✅ Add a swatch for each new token
<div className="space-y-2">
  <div className="h-16 rounded-lg bg-primary" />
  <p className="text-sm font-medium">primary</p>
</div>
```

Use the Tailwind class that maps to the token (e.g. `bg-background`, `text-muted-foreground`). Include a border on light swatches when needed for contrast.

## Icons → `icons.stories.tsx`

When importing a new icon from `react-icons` for use in the app, add it to the `catalog` array in `src/components/foundations/icons.stories.tsx`.

```tsx
// ✅ Import at top, then register in catalog
import { LuSparkles } from "react-icons/lu";

const catalog = [
  // ...existing entries
  { label: "LuSparkles", Icon: LuSparkles },
] as const;
```

Keep `label` matching the export name. Preview under **Foundations / Icons** in Storybook.
